reviewText:
Repetitive but a lot of fun. Don't yet understand why it's marketed as having coop and multiplayer; I couldn't find it. Still, good singleplayer game if you have no friends.

Adding more because this review got a little attention;
Sorry about small amount of hours. Doesn't take much to see all this game has to offer, though. There is a campaign with levels that vary only a little (new obstacles, different game modes here and there). Overall, you'll probably get bored pretty quick, but I'd still say to grab it on a sale if you know anyone IRL to play with.
